Rating: 3
I've made this recipe many times according to the directions. Though I generally loathe when people write a review of a recipe that has nothing to do with the original recipe itself, I will of course make an exception for myself! (smile) At the farmers market recently I found small, round, green Thai eggplants and decided to saute the eggplant and green beans (plus bell pepper) together over high heat and then finished by adding the dressing to steam everything for the final two minutes. I added the tomatoes and garnish before serving and it all turned out delicious. My adaptation tasted just like the original dish but was less like a salad.

